{"journal": "Neuropsychopharmacology", "PMID": "15127084", "method": [["The O-15-water PET activation method was used to map sustained and divided attention in 16 patients with Alzheimer\u2019s disease (mean age SD: 68 5 years; MMSE: 11\u201325, mean SD 19.5 4.9) and in 16 healthy age-matched control subjects.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": -1, "pred": ["was", "used"], "cds": {"patients": 1, "subjects": 1, "years": 1}, "sub": ["O-15-water", "PET", "activation", "method"], "nes": {}}, "sp": 0, "ne": 0, "cd": 158, "sid": "4", "total": 158, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Johannsen et al., (1999) - Cortical responses to sustained and divided attention in AD_annotated_ann.json"}], ["The MR volumes were automatically coregistered (Collins et al., 1994) within the Talairach coordinate system (Talairach and Tournoux, 1988) except for two patients in whom coregistration was performed manually (Neelin et al., 1993) due to cortical atrophy.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": -1, "pred": ["were"], "cds": {"patients": 1}, "sub": ["MR", "volumes"], "nes": {"Collins": 1, "Tournoux": 1, "Talairach": 2, "Neelin": 1}}, "sp": 0, "ne": 0, "cd": 126, "sid": "83", "total": 126, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Johannsen et al., (1999) - Cortical responses to sustained and divided attention in AD_annotated_ann.json"}]], "findings": [["The results from the healthy elderly (Johannsen et al., 1997) showed that sustained attention favored the parietal attention site, whereas divided attention activated the frontal site predominantly.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 90, "pred": ["showed"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["results"], "nes": {"Johannsen": 1}}, "sp": 2, "ne": 0, "cd": 0, "sid": "33", "total": 2, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Johannsen et al., (1999) - Cortical responses to sustained and divided attention in AD_annotated_ann.json"}], ["We report the statistical significant peaks together with anatomical homologous nonsignificant peaks in either the Alzheimer patient group or the control subjects group.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 142, "pred": ["report"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["We"], "nes": {"Alzheimer": 1}}, "sp": 2, "ne": 15, "cd": 0, "sid": "95", "total": 17, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Johannsen et al., (1999) - Cortical responses to sustained and divided attention in AD_annotated_ann.json"}], ["In the control subjects, the combined analysis of all attention tasks showed significant activation of the right middle frontal gyrus (BA-46 and BA-10), the inferior parietal lobule (BA-40), and the right medial frontal gyrus (BA-6) ( Table 3; Fig. 1A).", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 65, "pred": ["showed"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["analysis"], "nes": {}}, "sp": 3, "ne": 0, "cd": 0, "sid": "103", "total": 3, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Johannsen et al., (1999) - Cortical responses to sustained and divided attention in AD_annotated_ann.json"}], ["This study demonstrated a different cortical activation pattern in patients with Alzheimer\u2019s disease compared to healthy age-matched control subjects during sustained and divided attention.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 307, "pred": ["demonstrated"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["study"], "nes": {}}, "sp": 1, "ne": 0, "cd": 0, "sid": "127", "total": 1, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Johannsen et al., (1999) - Cortical responses to sustained and divided attention in AD_annotated_ann.json"}], ["In the overall analysis we found a significant activation of the anterior cingulate in the healthy elderly and a similar but nonsignificant increase in the patients.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 14, "pred": ["found"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["we"], "nes": {}}, "sp": 5, "ne": 0, "cd": 0, "sid": "158", "total": 5, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Johannsen et al., (1999) - Cortical responses to sustained and divided attention in AD_annotated_ann.json"}], ["In the healthy elderly, we found also that divided attention predominantly is associated with the frontal attention site (Johannsen et al., 1997).", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 14, "pred": ["found"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["we"], "nes": {"Johannsen": 1}}, "sp": 5, "ne": 0, "cd": 0, "sid": "176", "t